me.taylorkelly.mywarp.warp

Interface WarpManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EventfulWarpManager, MemoryWarpManager, StorageWarpManager

    public interface WarpManager
    Manages Warps and provides utility methods to get information based on the Warps managed by it.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • add

        void add(Warp warp)
        Adds the given Warp to this manager.
        Parameters:
        warp - the Warp

      • populate

        void populate(java.lang.Iterable<Warp> warps)
        Populates this manager with the given Warps. Unlike add(Warp) this method must only be used to populate the warp manager with already existing warps.
        Parameters:
        warps - the Warps

      • remove

        void remove(Warp warp)
        Deletes the given Warp from this manager.
        Parameters:
        warp - the warp

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clears this manager, removing all Warps previously managed by it. Unlike remove(Warp) this method must only be used to clear the warp manager, it does not represent a removal of a warp.

      • getSize

        int getSize()
        Gets the number of all Warps managed by this manger.
        Returns:
        the total number of Warps on this manager

      • contains

        boolean contains(java.lang.String name)
        Checks whether a Warp with the given name is managed by this manager.
        Parameters:
        name - the name
        Returns:
        true if this manager contains a warp with this name

      • get

        com.google.common.base.Optional<Warp> get(java.lang.String name)
        Gets an Optional containing the Warp of the given name managed by this manager, if such a Warp exists.
        Parameters:
        name - the exact name
        Returns:
        an Optional containing the Warp with the given name

      • filter

        java.util.Collection<Warp> filter(com.google.common.base.Predicate<Warp> predicate)
        Gets all Warps on this manager that fulfill the given Predicate. The returned collection is a live view, changes to one affect the other. If a live view is not needed, it may be faster to create a copy of the Warps returned by this method.
        Parameters:
        predicate - the predicate
        Returns:
        all Warps that fulfill the Predicate
